# Themes

If you want to set your ggplot theme globally (for the whole document) you can use this code: 


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
theme_set(theme_minimal())
```
:::


# Digits



# Colors

## Default Colors


::: {.cell layout-ncol="2" fig-cap-location='top'}

```{.r .cell-code}
bp <- ggplot(iris, aes(Species, Sepal.Length)) + 
  geom_boxplot(aes(fill = Species)) +
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(legend.position = "top")
bp

# Scatter plot
sp <- ggplot(iris, aes(Sepal.Length, Sepal.Width)) + 
  geom_point(aes(color = Petal.Length)) +
  theme_minimal()+
  theme(legend.position = "top")
sp
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![Boxplot Plot -- discrete colors](P_Colors_Themes_Scales_Notes_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-3-1.png){width=672}
:::

::: {.cell-output-display}
